Although it does occur to me - how does he know that your first meeting is going to be your last if he has no memory of the past? Maybe he recognizes that introductions mean he's never going to see you again
附加记录：    

.

Your future is his past. So after the first meeting (from your perspective) all other meetings must by definition occur in your future (his past) - ergo all other meetings must occur in his past.

In order for there to occur a meeting in his "unknown" future it would have to have occured in your perceived past - which is impossible if this is your first meeting.

At your last meeting all other meetings have occured in your past - his future. So he will not recognise you - it is for him your first meeting.

My mind hurts now..







