Nope. Here's how the convo goes MY perspective:

"Hi, I'm Legendary." - "Goodbye"

Here's how it goes HIS perspective.

"eybdooG", which is a standard greeting. - ".yradnegeL m'I ,iH", at which point he becomes emotionally distressed, but only then.

To expand:

I enter - His distress goes away, like magic.

And that's assuming I only intro myself that one time. I might introduce myself EVERY time I see him, to make sure he remembers my name, or only at the end, so he'll remember it in the past. (EDIT: And I'd only do that by prompting, because I wouldn't know it would be the last meeting. I'D be distressed leaving). Enough people do that that it's very likely he won't EVER be certain of last meetings, simply because the mechanics behind any conversation are already FUBAR.





